'''Almas''' was a [[Terraforming/Legends|terraformed]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]].<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref> Its [[Moon/Legends|moon]], [[Dorumaa]], was a captured satellite, which underwent its own terraforming.

==History==
An anomaly in itself, Almas was a molten, terrestrial planet orbiting beyond the usual range for its kind, and due to this it received little sunlight. Despite its hot core, Almas was not very geologically active. It had only two small mountain ranges. The planet's [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]] was initially filled with poisonous gases like [[Phosphorus/Legends|phosphorus]] and [[Methane/Legends|methane]], until [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Rivan]], aiming to settle there, developed the [[kaluthin]] grass to help alter the atmosphere. Almas had no surface water, but there were underground lakes upon which the kaluthin drew and to which settlers later built wells. The kaluthin was a success, given that all Almas' water was located underground, and thrived there for centuries.<ref name="LFC" /> On the leaves of the kaluthin were phosphorus deposits that glowed with a faint light. When the kaluthin covered the planet, these deposits gave the planet an "aura."

Over the centuries, the kaluthin spread across the planet and created a highly [[Oxygen/Legends|oxygen]]-rich atmosphere. However, trace amounts of phosphorus and methane could still have detrimental effects on those who spent extended time outside without a [[Breath mask/Legends|breath mask]]. The plants' kilometers-deep taproots also brought up heat from the planet's core, warming the surface. In addition, the purple-green grass gave the planet a distinct aural glow, mainly from the phosphorus it consumed. This living growth was unusually countered by the dark-side energy on the planet, which originated in the desert region and slowly spread. The [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] measured the spread to be one meter per year.<ref name="LFC" />

Darth Rivan built [[Almas Sith fortress|his Sith fortress]] there before [[1250 BBY]]. The castle was located on the desert side of the planet. It was built on this planet with the hopes of gathering [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark-side]] energy from the [[The Force/Legends|Force]]-dense [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]].<ref name="LFC" /> Here Darth Rivan tried to create a corps of [[Sith battlelord]]s, but his apprentice betrayed him before he could do so.<ref name="SB">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/livingforce/lf20050901sithbattlelords|text=Sith Battlelords}}</ref>

After decades of living there, Darth Rivan was expelled by the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] during the [[New Sith Wars]] in the [[Battle at Almas|Battle of Almas]]. Parts of the fortress were destroyed, but its core resisted blaster fire. The Jedi left the planet, ignoring the remains of the building.<ref name="LFC" />

[[File:The_Call_of_the_Cult_DaL.png|thumb|left|250px|A Believers camp erected around the Almas Sith fortress]]
The kaluthin, thriving even without Rivan, kept Almas from being worth mining. It grew everywhere besides near the Sith fortress, and its roots delved deep. What little mineral content the planet had was not worth the added expense of removing the kaluthin from a mining site. However, the planet became a gardenlike site instead of the nightmare it had been&mdash;except around the Sith Fortress, where no life could thrive. The kaluthin also processed the phosphorus and generated a glow that illuminated the planet from its surface instead of from the sky.<ref name="LFC" />

After [[Reidi Artom]] rediscovered the system in [[232 BBY/Legends|232 BBY]], two Jedi, master [[Qornah]] and his [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Kibh Jeen]], came to Almas to research Rivan's fortress. The Sith fortress corrupted Jeen, who slew his master, took over the [[Cularin asteroid belt|asteroid belt]] [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]], and started the [[Dark Jedi Conflict]] ([[188 BBY|188]]&ndash;[[181 BBY/Legends|181 BBY]]). After the Conflict, a Jedi school was founded, which grew into the [[Almas Academy]], the headmaster of which was [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Nerra Ziveri]], and then his former apprentice, Master [[Lanius Qel-Bertuk]].<ref name="LFC" />

The town of [[Forard]] grew up around the Academy. The Academy and Forard were built directly upon the kaluthin, which did not seem to affect the plant at all. There was also a kaluthin [[Forard research station]] near the town, where possible transplants of kaluthin to other planets were analyzed.<ref name="LFC" />

Almas was the only planet in the system not occupied by [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

In circa [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]], the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Garth Ezzar]] attacked Almas and [[Destruction of the Almas Academy|destroyed the Almas Academy]], killing most of the Jedi there.<ref name="Destruction">{{LivingForce|Heart of Evil: Destruction}}</ref>

Months after the Clone Wars, agents of [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Prestor Organa]] infiltrated the ruined temple of the Almas Academy, and found it infested by dark-side spirits. They retrieved a [[Holocron/Legends|holocron]] through which Jedi Master [[Denia]] learned [[Farsight/Legends|Farseeing]] techniques which enabled her to learn the identity of the [[Nazren]].<ref name="Echoes of the Jedi">{{DoD|Echoes of the Jedi}}</ref> The ruins and surrounding area were also home to the [[Dark Lizard]]s of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]], a species of [[Hssiss]] [[Reptile/Legends|dragon]] that was thoroughly permeated with the dark side of the Force.

{{RPG}}
During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] established a base on Almas, near the ruins of the Jedi Academy. Rumors of Alliance activity there reached the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], so [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Firmus Piett/Legends|Firmus Piett]] dispatched a group of Imperial agents to Almas to investigate. Shortly after the agents arrived, the [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] [[Platoon/Legends|platoon]] that had been assigned to protect them went missing. The agents soon found the Rebel base, but it was abandoned. It was covered under a large amount of foliage, and the Rebels had erected barricades to protect them from attack by Dark Lizards, [[Believers]] and [[t'salak]]s. A rescue party sent by the Alliance then arrived, and they assumed that the Imperials had caused the disappearance of all their comrades in the base.<ref name="RECG">''[[Rebellion Era Campaign Guide]]''</ref>
{{Endgame}}

Years were calculated on the planet and elsewhere in the Cularin system using the "[[After Artom]]" system of time measurement.<ref name="LFC" />

